<p>
<seg id=1> Kosovo's international observers are still hopeful for a revival of a ceasefire in spite of the continued fighting by Serbian security forces and Albanian separatists over the last few days. </seg>
<seg id=2> A spokesperson for the observers in Pristina said on Monday that Yugoslavia's province of Kosovo is currently quiet. </seg>
<seg id=3> Last week's fighting took the lives of twelve people. </seg>
<seg id=4> Bronislaw Geremek from Poland, the chairperson of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe, held that the violent conflict was caused by both sides engaged in the war. </seg>
</p>
